## Rules

### BACK-001: Constructor Injection Only
severity: ERROR
scope: all Spring-managed beans
rule: Field injection (`@Autowired` on fields) is prohibited. All dependencies MUST be injected via constructors. Constructor parameters MUST be declared `final`. Spring's `@RequiredArgsConstructor` is acceptable.
threshold: max_class_lines=300, max_method_lines=40
example_correct: |
  @Service
  public class OrderService {
      private final OrderRepository repo;
      public OrderService(OrderRepository repo) { this.repo = repo; }
  }
example_incorrect: |
  @Service
  public class OrderService {
      @Autowired private OrderRepository repo;  // field injection — prohibited
  }

### BACK-002: No Checked Exceptions in Service Layer
severity: ERROR
scope: all service and use-case classes
rule: Service methods MUST NOT declare checked exceptions in their signatures. Checked exceptions from lower layers MUST be wrapped in unchecked application exceptions. Exception messages MUST include enough context to identify the failing operation.
threshold: max_class_lines=300
example_correct: |
  public Order getOrder(Long id) {
      return repo.findById(id)
          .orElseThrow(() -> new OrderNotFoundException("Order " + id + " not found"));
  }
example_incorrect: |
  public Order getOrder(Long id) throws SQLException { ... }  // checked — prohibited
